        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 5:07PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 507 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sanford, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Midland around 515 PM EDT.
Linwood around 535 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Averill, Crump,
Bombay, Willard, Hope, and Bay City State Recreation Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
